# [NTP](../wg/ntp.html)

## Summary

The NTP Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss active drafts, experimental pool implementations, and progress on related security and timing standards. Key updates included welcoming Tommy as the incoming Area Director (AD), reviewing the RFC Editor queue, assessing interoperability testing from the IETF 126 Hackathon, and discussing the status of core drafts including `draft-ietf-ntp-ntpv5`, `draft-ietf-ntp-nts-keyexchange-pool`, and `draft-ietf-ntp-nts-for-ptp`. The working group also reviewed a liaison request from ITU Study Group 17 and proposed a virtual interim meeting in September.

